Serves 4Ingredients:200g paneer, cubed30ml (2 tbsp) cornflour30ml (2 tbsp) ghee or butter2 cinnamon sticks3 cardamom pods5ml (1 tsp) fennel seeds3 green chillies, sliced300g (1 cups) uncooked basmati rice, soaked in hot water for 1 hour, rinsed and drainedSalt, to tastePinch of saffron strands, soaked in 60ml ( cup) hot milkPaneer with cauli-rice & butter sauceMethod:1) Toss the paneer cubes in the cornflour to coat well, shaking off excess flour.2) Heat the ghee in a large pan and fry the paneer till lightly golden. Remove with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towel. 3) Fry the cinnamon sticks, cardamom pods, fennel seeds and chillies in the same pan for a few seconds till fragrant. Add the rice, a pinch of salt and 125ml ( cup) water. Reduce heat, cover and simmer until the water has been absorbed. If the rice is not yet tender, add a few more spoons of water and simmer till done.4) Fold in the paneer, saffron and milk and heat through.